
Blue-Green Deployment -

🔧 What It Is:
You run two full environments:
	• Blue = current version
	• Green = new version
Then, you instantly switch 100% of traffic from Blue to Green once Green is verified.
✅ Pros:
	• Zero downtime
	• Instant rollback (just point traffic back to Blue)
	• Easy to test new version before switching



Canary Deployment -

🔧 What It Is:
You gradually shift traffic to the new version (canary) in phases:
	1. Start with 5–10% of traffic
	2. Observe for errors/performance
	3. Slowly increase to 100%
✅ Pros:
	• Lower risk — issues impact only a small % of users
	• Real-world testing under real load
	• Can be automated and monitored






Here's how you can switch traffic from the blue deployment to the green deployment
	
	<kubectl edit svc myapp-service>
	
	--->  Modify and Re-apply the YAML
	
	<>
	---> kubectl apply -f service.yaml
	
	
	
	
	
	
	DaemonSet kya hota hai ?
	
	🗣️ "DaemonSet ek aisa object hai jo har node pe ek pod ko chalata hai."
	Matlab:
	
	Agar tumhare paas 5 nodes hain, to ek DaemonSet 5 pods banayega — har node pe ek.
	
	🧭 Real-life Example:
	Socho tum ek log collector (Filebeat, Fluentd) lagana chahte ho taaki har node ke logs collect ho sakein.
	Is case me tum DaemonSet use karte ho.
	
	📦 Use Cases (real examples):
		• Logs collect karna (Fluentd, Filebeat)
		• Node metrics lena (Prometheus Node Exporter)
		• Network setup (Calico, Cilium)
		• System monitoring tools
	
	🧾 Example YAML (basic):
	
	yaml
	CopyEdit
	apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: DaemonSet
metadata:
  name: my-daemonset
spec:
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: my-agent
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: my-agent
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: my-container
        image: busybox
        command: ["/bin/sh", "-c", "while true; do echo Running on $(hostname); sleep 10; done"]
	📝 Ye DaemonSet har node pe ek busybox container run karega jo bas echo karega.
	
	🧪 Commands:
	
	bash
	CopyEdit
	kubectl apply -f my-daemonset.yaml      # Deploy karo
kubectl get daemonset                   # List all DaemonSets
kubectl describe daemonset my-daemonset # Details dekho
kubectl delete daemonset my-daemonset   # Delete karo
